2. cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper involves converting decimal sequences into binary form, which is a numerical analysis task. 
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper may involve algorithms for converting decimal sequences into binary form and generating binary random sequences. 
4. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security): Binary random sequences are often used in cryptography and security applications, so this sub-category is also a possibility. 
5. cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper may involve software implementation of the algorithms for generating binary random sequences.
